University of Nebraska researcher has revealed why stress is bad for you in a video . 
  Limited periods of stress are good, as they release the hormone cortisol . 
  This is useful in helping you recover from tense situations . 
  But too much will lower your immune system and make your bones fragile . 
  The science of stress was explained by Dr Raychelle Burks from the University of Nebraska-Lincoln . 
  In it she reveals why stress can inhibit the immune system . 
 